{"id":79528,"title":"Getting essential health products to their end users: subsidize, but how much?","abstract":"Although coverage rates and health outcomes are improving, many poor people around the world still do not benefit from essential health products. An estimated two-thirds of child deaths could be prevented with increased coverage of products such as vaccines, point-of-use water treatment, iron fortification, and insecticide-treated bednets. What limits the flow of products from the producer's laboratory bench to the end users, and what can be done about it? Recent empirical research suggests a crucial role for heavy subsidies. ","date":"2014-09-12","categories":"Parasitic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25214612","annotations":[{"name":"Health","weight":0.812486,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Vaccine","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccine"},{"name":"Poverty","weight":0.688474,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poverty"},{"name":"Iron","weight":0.645267,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iron"},{"name":"Laboratory","weight":0.614351,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laboratory"},{"name":"Child","weight":0.537547,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child"},{"name":"Water","weight":0.482424,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water"},{"name":"Research","weight":0.445085,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research"},{"name":"Subsidy","weight":0.264836,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subsidy"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.259539,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Fortification","weight":0.23813,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortification"},{"name":"Water treatment","weight":0.180998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_treatment"},{"name":"Mosquito net","weight":0.136506,"wik